<h1>About Us</h1>
<p><strong>What’s the gist?</strong></p>
GreenCoin presents a mechanism by which the open market can collectively price carbon emissions. (note: carbon, carbon dioxide, and CO2 are used interchangeably in this FAQ)<br/><br/>

<p><strong>What is GreenCoin?</strong></p>
GreenCoin is a digital asset that captures the value of useful production and commerce that resulted in a reduced carbon dioxide emission impact.<br/><br/>

<p><strong>How are GreenCoins produced?</strong></p>
There are two ways to produce GreenCoins:<br/>
  • GreenCoins are awarded to miners (more on mining here)<br/>
  • GreenCoins are awarded to commerce producers who have registered with the GreenCoin network.<br/><br/>

<p><strong>Why carbon (as opposed to any other type of pollution mitigation)?</strong></p>
Carbon is the ultimate global issue and it requires a global solution. Carbon isn’t toxic, so there is no immediate incentive to be the one guy who doesn’t drive an SUV to work. Only in its global aggregation does it present catastrophic environmental harm. In the past, governments have attempted to work together to solve the issue to varying degrees of success and failure, and a permanent global solution is currently not really on the table. One criticism is the drag on the economy that punitive Cap & Trade regulations may have. However, the other side if this equation is the drag on the economy the environmental damage costs from global warming’s adverse effects.  Governments try to gauge the two side of this equation for setting Cap & Trade regulations. However, governments are less efficient than market based pricing methods. Therefore, a voluntary, market-based way to price and trade carbon is required in order to solve this menacing issue.<br/>

