<p><strong>Is GreenCoin divisible?</strong></p>
The GreenCoin mechanism allows it to be divisible to 8 decimal units. However, the exchange to cash out GreenCoins may have a dollar minimum to limit traffic by eliminating transaction “dust.” Given that GreenCoin is a digital asset, technically speaking it is nearly infinitely divisible. The GreenCoin Foundation will determine the number sub decimal units to divide GreenCoin into based on the market price, as necessary to operate an exchange that is available to all market participants, from time-to-time and on a long-period basis.

<p><strong>How can I trust this mechanism?</strong></p>
The GreenCoin Foundation is intentionally set up as a not-for-profit entity. It will ultimately be governed by a Board and Operators that include top-executive renewable industry leaders, government entities, and not-for-profit organizations that operate in the traditional energy, cleantech, transportation, agriculture, forestry and other relevant spaces. The Foundation has the responsibility of maintaining the integrity of the system, assigning the GreenCoin algorithm (distributing GreenCoins pro rata to carbon reduction) auditing the renewable producers, providing public trust about the capped nature of the digital asset, and in general maintaining the honest and transparent operation of the system’s mechanics.

